 the regional, local, and "global" economies during the eight centuries of its existence. Sidebotham analyzes many of the artifacts, botanical and faunal remains, and hundreds of the texts he and his team found in excavations, providing a profoundly intimate glimpse of the people who lived, worked, and died in this emporium between the classical Mediterranean world and Asia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zEgyptzBarānīs. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zEgyptzBarānīs. 0aInternational tradexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPort citieszEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSpice tradezEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSpice tradezEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aTrade routeszEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aTrade routeszEgyptzBarānīsxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient buildings.  aancient city.  aancient rome.  aancient trade.  aancient travelers.  aarabia.  aarchaeological sites.  aarchaeology.  aasia.  abaranis.  aberenike.  achristianity.  acommerce.  acommercial networks.  aeastern desert.  aegypt.  aegyptology.  aexcavations.  aindian ocean.  amaritime trading.  amediterranean world.  amediterranean.  amiddle east.  amonsoons.  anile.  anonfiction.  aport cities.  aptolemy.  ared sea.  areligion.  aroman empire.  aroman soldiers.  aserapis temple.  asilk road.  asphinx.  aspice route.  aspice trade.  atrade routes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024430640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094838940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948389/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of Californ